Package examples

Interface Summary
ExampleURIs Utility interface that contains often used URIs of exemplary OWL ontologies as well as OWL-S services.
 

Class Summary
CreateComplexProcess This example shows how to create a complex process model that is shown in the file FindCheaperBook.owl .
CreateJavaGrounding This example shows how to create a service grounded to a simple Java method.
CreateSequence An example to show how service descriptions can be created on the fly, saved and executed.
ExecutionMonitor  
ForEachExample Example to show how to create and execute a forEach control construct.
Matchmaker An simple form of a semantic matchmaker that finds service matches for composition.
Matchmaker.Match  
OWLSExtensions An example demonstrating the extensibility features of the API.
OWLSExtensions.ExtendedProfile An extension to existing Profile implementation to return contact information.
OWLSExtensions.ExtendedProfileConverter A simple converter that will wrap existing OWLIndividuals as ExtendedProfile objects.
OWLSExtensions.OwnerConverter A simple converter that will wrap existing OWLIndividuals as OwnerEntity objects.
OWLSExtensions.OwnerEntity A wrapper around an OWLIndividual that defines utility functions to access Owner information defined in FLAServiceOnt ontology.
OWLSValidator Validate OWL-S service descriptions to find errors such as flaws in the data flow specification, grounding description and so on.
PreconditionCheck Example to show how precondition check works.
PreconditionUsage Example to show how precondition check can be used to find valid values.
RunAllExamples Just calls most of the examples in one go to be used as some sort of test before updating core parts of the API to ensure (!) correctness and soundness of changes.
RunService Examples to show how services can be executed.
ServiceExtension Another example demonstrating the extensibility features of the API.
ServiceExtension.ExtendedService An extension to existing Service implementation extended by an additional property.
ServiceExtension.ExtendedServiceConverter A simple converter that will wrap existing OWLIndividuals as ExtendedProfile objects.
ServiceParameterExample This example shows how to access Profile.getServiceParameters() and Profile.getCategories() values.
Translator Read a service description written in one version and print the description in another version.
WSDL2OWLS A simple to GUI to create OWL-S files from WSDL descriptions.
